news.title: Nashik civic body to inspect status of rainwater harvesting systems
news.para: As per norms, the rainwater harvesting system is mandatory for residential and commercial buildings constructed on a land measuring 500 square metres and above.

news.title: Now, app on conveyance deed process in Maharashtra
news.para: In simple terms, the conveyance deed or deemed conveyance refers to the transfer of land in the name of the housing society from the builder.

news.title: Enforcement wing of Jaipur development body razes two illegal colonies
news.para: The first land was recovered in Abhaypura Village on Kaupra Wala Road under the jurisdiction of zone 11. Builders were constructing a colony named Balaji Vihar without mandatory land conversion.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA issues RCs worth over Rs 23 crore against two builders over dues
news.para: Additional CEO Aditi Singh said RCs worth Rs 23.39 crore were issued by the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) against developers Assotech Realty and AVJ Homes.

news.title: Now, camps in your area for property tax collection in Gurugram
news.para: The corporation aims to collect Rs 1,100 crore from property tax alone in the current fiscal year, of which it has been able to collect just 16.3% — Rs 180 crore — so far, according to MCG officials.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body housing scheme survey lifts veil off 14 plots worth Rs 10 crore
news.para: The cash-strapped development authority has discovered 14 land parcels spanning 2,000sqm in total following a survey of its Swarn Jayanti Puram housing scheme.

news.title: HDFC gets an all-cash offer from Omkara ARC for bad loan portfolio
news.para: According to sources, three to four large asset reconstruction companies examined the portfolio, but HDFC ultimately received a bid from Omkara ARC for the entire pool. HDFC is currently evaluating the bid, and a decision is expected in the coming weeks.

news.title: Deloitte inks one million sq ft of office lease in Bengaluru
news.para: The firm has leased around 500,000 sq ft of office space at Prestige Tech Park on Outer Ring Road and over 460,000 sq ft in SalarpuriaAura and Eminence in Bengaluru.

news.title: Rare Asset Reconstruction & Naman Group gets the vote for Rajesh Lifespaces' hotel unit
news.para: The Rare-Naman Group consortium had offered ₹461 crore upfront in cash with another ₹31 crore in equity, making it the preferred bidder for lenders, ET reported in its February 27 edition.

news.title: BMC can't demand 100% consent of tenants for redevelopment: Bombay HC
news.para: The BMC cannot impose such a requirement when the state’s Development Control Regulations call for 50%-70% consent in redevelopment projects, saidl a bench of Justices Girish Kulkarni and R N Laddha.

news.title: Lower mortgage rates boost US home sales in February
news.para: The jump in sales of previously owned homes, which was reported by the National Association of Realtors on Tuesday, was the largest in more than 2-1/2 years and ended 12 straight monthly declines in sales, the longest such stretch since 1999.

news.title: Issue OC to Patra Chawl free-sale building: Bombay HC to Mhada
news.para: The free sale component construction continued and at least two of the three towers made by Ekta Everglade Homes Pvt Ltd are complete and awaiting OC.

news.title: Sobha shares plunge 4% as Income Tax department raids premises
news.para: The Nifty Realty index tracked the overall positive sentiments in the markets and was trading at 396.45, up 1.75 points or 0.44%. The top gainers were Oberoi Realty, The Phoenix Mills and Macrotech Developers.

news.title: Now, government employees can buy plots in smart townships across Andhra Pradesh
news.para: This will help employees purchase sites in layouts developed by urban development authorities anywhere in the state irrespective of the district they are working.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to bring unassessed buildings under property tax ambit in a year
news.para: According to a KMC revenue department official, mayor Firhad Hakim has instructed the department to make all assessment department officials accountable for assessment of unassessed buildings and arrange for mutation of properties.
